{"questionId":"10404","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Both vinegar (a dilute aqueous solution of ethanoic acid) and bleach are used as cleaning agents.</span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Bleach reacts with ammonia, also used as a cleaning agent, to produce the poisonous compound chloramine, NH<sub>2</sub>Cl.</span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Deduce the molecular geometry of chloramine and estimate its H–N–H bond angle.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Molecular geometry:</span></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">H–N–H bond angle:</span></span></span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><em>Molecular geometry</em>:<br>«trigonal» pyramidal &nbsp; <strong>[✔]</strong><br></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><em>H–N–H bond angle</em>:<br>107° &nbsp;&nbsp; <strong style=\"color:#000000;font-family:Verdana , Arial , Helvetica , sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:bold;letter-spacing:normal;text-align:left;text-decoration:none;text-indent:0px;white-space:normal;\">[✔]</strong><br></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><strong>Note</strong>:&nbsp;Accept angles in the range of 100–109.</span></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"10404","referenceCode":"19M.2.hl.TZ1.5c(iii)","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Deduce the molecular geometry of chloramine and estimate its H–N–H bond angle. Molecular geometry: H–N–H bond angle:","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"c(iii)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 4: Chemical bonding and structure","4.3 Covalent structures","Core","Topic 4: Chemical bonding and structure"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}